text: Katinka Larsen (9 November 1905 - August 1999) was a female diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== Larsen competed for England in the 3 Metres Springboard at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. She won a silver medal in the 3 Metres Springboard Diving at the 1934 European Aquatics Championships. She also competed at the 1936 Summer Olympics. ==Personal life== She married Edward F W Tinsley in 1937. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1905 births Category:1999 deaths Category:English female divers Category:Divers at the 1934 British Empire Games Category:Olympic divers of Great Britain Category:Divers at the 1936 Summer Olympics
